      "description": "Requires that all Hawaiian names and words included in letterheads, symbols, and emblems of the State and counties include accurate and appropriate Hawaiian spelling and punctuation. Establishes references for accurate, appropriate, and authentic Hawaiian names and words, including proper Hawaiian spelling and punctuation. Requires DAGS to adopt procedures by rule to verify the compliance. Effective 07\/01\/2050. (SD2)"
