      "description": "Establishes a three-year pilot program to generate revenue for the use of public school land. Specifies that the lieutenant governor, in consultation with the department of education, board of education, and other appropriate agencies, shall be the facilitator of the pilot program. Authorizes the lease of certain public school lands for public purposes, including but not limited to the development of workforce housing rental units, under specified conditions. Establishes the school facilities special fund within chapter 302A, HRS. Repeals the schools facilities special fund in chapter 171C, HRS. Requires the lieutenant governor to submit a report to the legislature. Makes an appropriation for the pilot program. Pilot program repeals 6\/30\/2016."
