      "last_action_date": "2014-01-21",
      "last_action": "Referred to JDL.",
      "title": "Abuse of Family or Household Members; Probable Cause Hearing; Domestic Violence Intervention Programs",
      "description": "Requires the court to hold a separate probable cause hearing, when a person is charged with the offense of abuse of a family or household member or refusal to comply with the lawful order of a police officer, to review the charge and determine if there is probable cause to believe that the person charged will benefit from undergoing domestic violence intervention programs."
